      "description": "This 993-generation Carrera is a superlative example of air-cooled engineering. Powered by the M64 3.6L flat-six featuring a dry-sump lubrication system, the powerplant is mated to the highly sought-after G50 six-speed manual transaxle. The mechanical integrity is absolute, with zero weeping from the chain covers and perfect synchromesh engagement. The chassis retains its original LSA multi-link rear suspension geometry and four-piston monobloc calipers, offering the tactile feedback and kinematic precision expected of a concours-level machine. This is a turn-key, investment-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
